{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1a7bc345-21ad-4220-bcf6-786db59cad68","content":"You're all set. Since `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` is already referenced, use the `--hotreload` flag with `dotnet test`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in watch mode. When you save changes to your source or test files, it automatically re-runs the affected tests **without a full rebuild**, giving you a much faster feedback loop.\n\n**Tips:**\n- Keep the terminal open while you edit `EmailValidatorTests.cs` (or the code under test).\n- On each save, only the changed tests re-execute.\n- Press `Ctrl+C` to exit when you're done.\n\nThis is significantly faster than repeatedly running `dotnet test` manually because it hot-patches the running process instead of doing a cold build each time.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dab0ad88-c5c2-4a15-98ca-654ef4d5306c","outputTokens":185,"requestId":"B452:101CE8:E9A56F:F7757E:6A044D5A"},"id":"a09cb6df-182a-41f4-bacb-f0dea5cce4e7","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:33.214Z","parentId":"1fbd68b5-8d6e-45b5-9201-f5cbc0e2e907"}
